BSE, IFST POSITION STATEMENT UPDATE - UK
*****************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed/html>
See Also
BSE, IFST position statement - UK 980403065945
BSE, IFST position statement update - UK 981127001541
Date: Tue, 15 Jun 1999 23:38:15 GMT
From: jralphb@easynet.co.uk (J Ralph Blanchfield)

Please note that IFST, through its Technical and Legislative Committee and
Public Affairs Committee, has issued an updated version, dated 16 June
1999, of its Position Statement on BSE.
This has the same Web address as the previous version, and is accessible
from the IFST Web site "hot topics" link
http://www.easynet.co.uk/ifst/hottop.htm
The Position Statement may be accessed directly at
http://www.easynet.co.uk/ifst/hottop5.htm
This is linked to the Legislation Appendix at
http://www.easynet.co.uk/ifst/hottop5l.htm
This message is being posted on several relevant food-related listservs and
newsgroups. Usual apologies to multiple subscribers who will thereby
receive more than one copy.
When visiting IFST's multiple-Award-winning Web site -- home page
<http://www.easynet.co.uk/ifst/> -- please take the opportunity to visit
other "hot topic" pages and the many other on-site food science and
technology goodies.
--
J Ralph Blanchfield, MBE
Food Science, Food Technology & Food Law Consultant
Chair, IFST External Affairs
Web Editor, Institute of Food Science & Technology
IFST Web address <http://www.easynet.co.uk/ifst/>
